message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a fully automated two-stage framework for pancreas segmentation based on convolutional neural networks (CNN). This work involves medical image analysis, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the use of CNNs is a common technique in medical image analysis, which is also related to the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.MED). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for pancreas segmentation using 3D CNNs, which is related to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NEURON).
